    <div class="article-teaser">
        Due to track replacement work on the Northern line no trains will run between East Finchley and High Barnet/Mill Hill East on Saturdays and Sundays, 10-11 and 17-18 December 2005.
        
    </div>



 <div class="on-this-page">
<div class="pullquote right">
                        <p>
                            Valid Underground tickets will be accepted on local bus services
                            
                        </p>
                    </div>
                
            
            
            
<p>Transport for London (TfL) is investing &pound;10 billion over the next 
five years to improve and expand London's transport network, with more than half 
of that going into the Tube.</p>
<p>The track improvement works are being carried out by Tube Lines, who are 
responsible for the maintenance and renewal of the Northern line.</p>
<p><h2>Bus services</h2></p>
<p>Two Rail Replacement Bus Services will be running on these weekends:</p>
<ul>
<li>Service A - Every 5-10 minutes between East Finchley and High Barnet, 
calling at all stations. For Totteridge and Whetstone Station the bus will call 
at Whetstone High Road 
</li><li>Service B - East Finchley - Finchley Central - Mill Hill East every 15 
minutes</li></ul>
<p>Valid Underground tickets will be accepted on local bus services.</p>
<p>Passengers should allow an extra 30 minutes for their journeys particularly 
late at night in order to make their connections with last trains. <br></p>
<hr>

